<h2 id='sub-11-6' class='sec-h2'><span>11.6 Risk Assessment</span> <em class='brass'>(12)</em></h2>
<table class='tbl'>
<thead><tr>
<th><strong>Risk</strong></th>
<th><strong>Severity</strong></th>
<th><strong>Mitigation / test approach</strong></th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Monthly invoice generation fails for 150+ contracts due to governor limits</td>
<td><strong>high</strong></td>
<td>Implement batch processing in Scheduled Flow, test with TC-PERF-002 (150 contracts), monitor SOQL/DML limits</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Duplicate invoices generated if Monthly_Invoice_Generation runs multiple times in same month</td>
<td><strong>high</strong></td>
<td>Billing_Period__c uniqueness check in flow, test with TC-008-01-05</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Vehicle status not synced when contract status changes, causing data inconsistency</td>
<td><strong>high</strong></td>
<td>Flow: Contract_Vehicle_Status_Sync with error handling, test with TC-002-01-04, TC-002-02-03</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Unauthorized users access PII fields (GDPR violation)</td>
<td><strong>high</strong></td>
<td>FLS enforcement on Account.National_IDc, Driver_License_Numberc, Date_of_Birth__c; Permission Set: GDPR_Data_Access required; test with TC-011-01-01, TC-011-01-02</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Mileage anomaly not detected, allowing incorrect vehicle mileage updates</td>
<td><strong>medium</strong></td>
<td>Flow: Mileage_Anomaly_Detection validates reading &gt; current mileage, test with TC-009-02-04</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Maintenance alerts duplicated if scheduled flow runs multiple times</td>
<td><strong>medium</strong></td>
<td>Alert_Sent__c flag prevents duplicates, test with TC-003-03-03, TC-004-01-03</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Mobile app fails to submit problem reports due to network issues</td>
<td><strong>medium</strong></td>
<td>Implement offline storage in LWC, retry logic; manual testing required (TC-009-01-01)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Insurance policy coverage limit exceeded but not flagged</td>
<td><strong>high</strong></td>
<td>Flow: Insurance_Policy_Claim_Aggregation sets Coverage_Limit_Exceeded__c flag, test with TC-007-02-04</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Bulk operations (200+ records) cause governor limit exceptions</td>
<td><strong>medium</strong></td>
<td>Bulkify all triggers and flows, test with TC-PERF-001, TC-PERF-003</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Field Audit Trail not enabled for PII fields, no GDPR compliance audit</td>
<td><strong>high</strong></td>
<td>Enable Field Audit Trail for Account.National_IDc, Driver_License_Numberc, Date_of_Birth__c; validate with TC-011-01-03</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Contract expiration alerts not reset when End_Date__c extended</td>
<td><strong>medium</strong></td>
<td>Flow: Contract_Alert_Reset clears Expiration_Alert_Sentc on End_Datec update, test with TC-005-01-03</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Incident_Date__c validation allows future dates, causing data integrity issues</td>
<td><strong>medium</strong></td>
<td>Validation Rule: Incident_Date_Not_Future, test with TC-006-01-04</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</section>
